This program had nothing to do with the city summer baseball/softball program or any program that may be offered through the AHHS athletics booster club.

Our school will have the chance to make a difference in education on February 7th! Learn why our participation in NAEP is important at http://1.usa.gov/1kVxTKI.

A group of our 8th-graders will represent thousands of others across the country on Februrary 7, 2019! Known as The Nation’s Report Card, NAEP is the largest nationally representative and continuing assessment of what students in the United States know and can do in a variety of subjects. Learn more at http://1.usa.gov/1jVs1Wt.

text: Students kindergarten through sixth grade had a chance to create a disguise to save their turkey from being found on the Thanksgiving plate. Go to www.alcesterhudsonlibrary.weebly.com/events to see all the creative submissions from our elementary students.
